<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="molten-cake" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Molten Chocolate Cake (Mug)</title>

  <p>
    Ingredients:
  </p>
  <tabular>
    <row>
      <cell>4 tablespoons butter</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>2 ounces bittersweet chocolate, divided</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{4}</m> cup sugar</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
    <cell>2 eggs</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>2 tablespoons cocoa powder</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>1 teaspoon vanilla</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{4}</m> teaspoon salt</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{4}</m> cup flour</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{2}</m> teaspoon baking powder</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>All microwaving is at 50% power</cell>
    </row>
  </tabular>

  <p>Instructions
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          Microwave butter and 1 ounce chocolate in large bowl, stirring often, until melted, about 1 minute. Whisk sugar, eggs, cocoa, vanilla, and salt into chocolate mixture until smooth. In separate bowl, combine flour and baking powder. Whisk flour mixture into chocolate mixture until combined. Divide batter evenly between 2 (11-ounce) coffee mugs.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Place mugs on opposite sides of microwave turntable. Microwave at 50 percent power for 50 seconds. Stir batter and microwave at 50 percent power for 30 seconds (or until batter rises to just below rim of mug). Press other ounce of chocolate, split in two pieces, into center of each cake until chocolate is flush with top of cake. Microwave at 50 percent power for 35 seconds (cake should be slightly wet around edges of mug and somewhat drier toward center). Let cakes rest for 2 minutes. Serve.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </p>

  <p>
    Notes:
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>
          You may have to adjust microwave times according to your oven.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          For one mug, halve ingredients.  First microwave should be 35 seconds; second microwave should be 10 seconds; last microwave should be 35 seconds.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </p>
</section>